Let [`x^{[$m]}\cdot x^{a}=x^{[$n]}\text{,}`] where [`a`] is a natural number. How many possibilities are there for [`a\text{?}`]

[_]{'1'}{10}

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Let [`x^{[$m]}\cdot x^{a}=x^{[$n]}\text{.}`] Then [`a`] must be [`[$n]-[$m]\text{.}`] So there is only one possibility for [`a\text{.}`]

